Easiest win: Count Good Nodes In Binary Tree
Simple DFS: pass a max value down, compare at each node. Good warm-up and quick.
Very common in interviews: Kth Smallest Element In a BST
In-order traversal (recursive or iterative); once you see “BST + kth smallest” → in-order, it’s straightforward.
If you want a bit more: Binary Tree Right Side View
Like level-order but only keep the last node per level. Reuses the BFS/level-order idea.